retirement plan or from individual accounts.
</P>
<P>
   The same reader also asked for advice on which mutual funds to
pick for her family's retirement plan. I can't give that kind of
detailed investment advice. Better to hire a professional or to
readahiti,' you can't do anything about it,'' Rausch said. ``You do
have to think about whether you trust your child and will be able
to teach them that this is important.''
</P>
<P>
   An education IRA might be a better idea, if the point is to save
for college or any other pre-retirement goal, Rausch added.
</P>
<P>
   There are tax consequences, said Larry W. Nichols, a certified
public accountant in Atlanta. Baby-sitting fees are self-employment
income. If it comes to more than $400, the income is subject to
self-employment tax.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you tried to say, 'I made $2,000 baby-sitting,' and if the
Internal Revenue Service checks that, they might say, 'Where's the
self-employment tax?' '' Nichols said.
</P>
<P>
   Hank Ezell writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution, Atlanta,
Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
