</P>
<P>
   R-MOVIES-TEENS _ The biggest challenge to movie theaters' pledge
to keep young teens out of R-rated movies opens today. It's ``South
Park: Bigger, Longer and Uncut,'' an R-rated summer movie that many
young kids want desperately to see. And what is it about? Wouldn't
you know it _ Stan, Kyle, Kenny and Cartman sneak into an R-rated,
which ultimately leads to war between the U.S. and Canada. Hot on
its heels will be ``American Pie,'' a raunchy R-rated film about
high school kids desperately seeking sex. We talk to young
moviegoers, parents and theater owners about the new policy,
whether its working, who's trying to beat it and what it all means.
(Blake/Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
