<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES30-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SHORTTAKES: Visit to the Mouse King
 &HT;    By Arnold Rosenfeld
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   I gave my granddaughter, Mira, a video of ``The Nutcracker''
ballet for her third birthday a couple of days ago. Mira is very
big on ballet. We watched it together.
</P>
<P>
   Mira got a little tense when the Mouse King turned up with his
Mouse army. I offered to fast-forward through the scary parts.
``Maybe it will turn out all right,'' she said, considering the
options.
</P>
<P>
   She asked a lot of questions.
</P>
<P>
   Q: ``Papa, she's a lady pretending to be a girl pretending to be
a lady?''
</P>
<P>
   A: ``Ummm, yes.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: ``Papa, is he (Drosselmeyer) a good guy or a bad guy?''
</P>
<P>
   A: ``Ummm, all uncles are good guys.'' (Mine were, hers are.
Yes, I know he's a godfather, but try explaining that.)
</P>
<P>
   Q: ``Papa, is he (Mouse King) a good guy or a bad guy?''
</P>
<P>
   A: ``Ummm, he's a pretend bad guy.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: ``Papa, do you know everything?''
</P>
<P>
   This grandfather gig isn't as bad as it's made out to be.
</P>
<P>
   Arnold Rosenfeld is editor-in-chief of the Cox Newspapers.
E-mail: arnold.rosenfeld(at)cox.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
