and walks a moderate line on immigration issues. By Richard L.
Berke.
</P>
<P>
   SC-GAMBLE (Columbia, S.C.) _ The South Carolina legislature is
expected today to approve a ballot question that would require
elimination of or regulation of video poker across the state. As
one of the few states without any such regulation, South Carolina
now has the dubious distinction of having more video poker machines
than any other state in the country, including Las Vegas _ a
situation anti-gambling forces decry. By David Firestone.
</P>
