<P>
   HISPANICS-GEORGIA _ ATLANTA _ Gov. Roy Barnes announces an
effort to get Hispanic Georgians to register to vote _ an
initiative that could very well assist the governor's choice in
next year's presidential campaign, Vice President Al Gore.
Three-fourths of new Hispanic voters tend to register and vote
Democratic. Regardless, in Georgia and elsewhere, they are a key
bloc in the 2000 elections. At the same time, Barnes is seeking to
elevate Hispanics' status in state politics by appointing a group
to recommend legislation next year to boost Hispanic interests.
(Judd, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
