<P>
   TV-NOTES (Undated) _ News and notes on television. By Bill
Carter and Lawrie Mifflin.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;  (``s'' code)
</P>
<P>
   TEN-WIMBLEDON (Wimbledon, England) _ Despite a rainy afternoon,
Wimbledon tries to complete its fourth-round matches in the men's
draw. Scheduled to play: Pete Sampras, who is going for his sixth
Wimbledon title; Boris Becker vs. Pat Rafter, a matchup of two
classic serve-and-volleyers at different stages of their careers,
and the completion of the Tim Henman-Jim Courier match. By Robin
Finn.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-DRAFT (New York) _ The National Basketball Association
season is over; the future _ in the form of the draft _ is
tomorrow. A look at the players who are expected to be among the
top 10 selections, a list that includes high schoolers,
high-profile Duke underclassmen and foreigners who have starred in
European leagues. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-TIGERS (New York) _ Detroit at the Yankees, 7:35 p.m.
ET start. By Jack Curry.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-MARLINS (Miami) _ N.Y. Mets at Florida, 7:05 p.m. ET
start. By Jason Diamos.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other stories
from our partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston Globe, Cox News
Service, Hearst Newspapers, The Houston Chronicle, The Arizona
Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles
Daily News, San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
