<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FRENCH-DISCO-PRIMER-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OOO-OUI! HERE'S HOW TO ACT FRENCH
</HEADLINE>
 
(Accompanies BC-FRENCH-DISCO, BC-FRENCH-DISCO-GLANCE) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Clueless about how to act French while dancing to French disco?
You're lucky you have us to help. Here's a quick primer:
</P>
<P>
   1. Well, speak French. Your local community college surely
offers summer courses in French, such as French grammar, elementary
French, and reading in French. Make the call.
</P>
<P>
   2. Wear a beret. In the wintertime, they're available at most
department stores. In the summertime, your best bet's gonna be
someplace like an Army-Navy store that specializes in military
clothes, including military berets. They go for $6-$14.
</P>
<P>
   3. At the bar, order a Pernod or Ricard, French
anisette-flavored liqueur drinks. Most bars have 'em.
</P>
<P>
   4. Sneer. Smoke clove cigarettes. Act superior. Pretend you
don't understand anyone speaking English. Yeah, we know that's a
stereotype, but then again, we've recently been to Paris.
</P>
<P>
   _ MALCOLM MAYHEW nn
</P>
</TEXT>
