<P>
   KOSOVO-FLORA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ For more than a decade, Flora Brovina peacefully, but
openly, protested Serbian atrocities against ethnic Albanian women
and children in Kosovo. Perhaps, friends and family say, she became
too fearless. In April _ a month after NATO began airstrikes on
Yugoslavia _ Serbian police arrested the woman whom Kosovar orphans
affectionately call ``Mother Flora.'' Brovina reportedly was
beaten, possibly tortured, and is partially paralyzed in a
Yugoslavian prison hospital. Now her son is waging an international
campaign to win her release. By KAREN ROUSE. Story has moved in
``i'' international category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   N A T I O N A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-CAMPAIGN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DTK _ With Texas Gov. George W. Bush on his first campaign swing
through California. By JAY ROOT. Story will move in ``a'' general
news and ``p'' political categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-GALLERY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FREDERICKSBURG, Texas _ The Admiral Nimitz Historical Center has
just dedicated a new $3 million National Museum of the Pacific War.
The 23,000 square-foot gallery in which the exhibits are displayed
is called the George Bush Gallery. The former president was on hand
for the dedication last week. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in
``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
