<P>
   AOL-UPGRADE _ America Online launches plans for the newest
version, AOL 5.0. Interview with AOL about what these changes will
mean for AOL. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BELLSOUTH _ The nibbling at the meat of BellSouth's market goes
on. A slew of competitive local exchange carriers _ CLECs _ are
continuing to take business away from the predominant phone
company. Although nearly all are targeting businesses and not
consumers, that strategy aims at the most lucrative _ and most
vulnerable _ part of BellSouth's market. (Kannell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CNN _ CNN will launch Thursday a $25 million ad campaign, the
largest and most comprehensive in its history. The thrust is to
re-assert the power of its brand among its core audience of
affluent baby boomers. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HDEPOT-WEB _ Home Depot unveils its first attempt at electronic
commerce. Official announcement scheduled for tomorrow, but we'll
find out today what the company will initially sell online. Home
Depot has been slow to jump on the Web, held back by pricing and
shipping issues. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-EXPERTS _ Medical experts in the Belgian town where
children first became ill after drinking Coke are not buying the
company's explaination that some of the kids were faking it. The
doctors who examined the kids say the illnesses were real.
(Roughton, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   w/COKE-DISCRIM _ Possible development in the race discrimination
lawsuit against Coca-Cola Co. A hearing on the company's motion to
dismiss the lawsuit has been set for July 15. (Unger/Rankin,
Atlanta journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MAC-CHANGES _ Imagine a Mac that several users could share, with
each maintaining a different configuration of folders, applications
and even desktop patterns. And what if that shared Mac could switch
among these individual configurations based on the voice of the
user? Such power is part of the latest upgrade to the Mac OS.
(Haddad, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   MINDSPRING _ MindSpring and Covad are expected today to announce
an expansion of their deal to provide high-speed lines (Digital
Subcriber Loops, a.k.a. DSL). The deal to be announced today calls
for high-speed options for consumers in Texas and California. Covad
and MindSpring already have an arrangement to provide DSL for
business customers in those states. In Atlanta, MindSpring has a
DSL deal with BellSouth. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
12.
</P>
<P>
   MP3 _ Record companies make deal with online MP3 music download
providers. This story tries to hone in on the local angle: how this
affects MP3.com and Cox Interactive which has a 10 per cent stake
in MP3.com _ do not confuse the Web site with the technology.
(Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HUFFY _ Huffy Corp., which for decades has manufactured
human-powered machines, has dipped its toe in the market for
electric-powered vehicles and likes the response so far. So much so
that it has partnered up with ZAP to co-market the companies'
electric-powered products. (Townsend, Dayton Daily News). 13.
</P>
<P>
   NCR-POSTAL _ NCR Corp. has landed a $67 million contract to
provide point-of-sales terminals to the U.S. Postal Service. Still,
lagging hardware sales prompted Merrill Lynch to lower its earnings
estimate for the company. (Bischoff, Dayton Daily News). 10
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ ATLANTA _ Mail and e-mail from readers are a
blessing. Your questions keep us at the newspaper in touch with
what you really need, and you let us know when you need to know
more about topics we've covered. Here are some of the questions
you've raised recently. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS PAGE
</P>
<P>
   CoxNet WHEELS 0629_ The thrill of putting the top down in
Porsche's new 911. Only one thing about the convertibles that
Porsche builds hasn't changed or been upgraded by technological
advances in 50 years of motorcar making: the simple fun of driving
a topless car. It doesn't matter whether it's a shiny six-figure
exotic from abroad or a rusting three-figure junker from the
classifieds, a convertible brings excitement to driving like
nothing else _ and the Porsche 911 Carrera Cabriolet does it with
exceptional grace. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   w/PBOX _ Porsche 911 stat box.
</P>
<P>
   NORA _ Nora Carter column. A/C retrofit not always a good idea.
WITH SIG
</P>
<P>
   END OF PAGE
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ A review of the Honday Odyssey minivan. (Sharp,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE-SILVERADO _ A test drive in the Chevrolet Silverado
pickup (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
