   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-EXPOS _ MONTREAL _ Braves at Montreal game story.
(Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: First pitch is at 7:05 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-NOTES _ MONTREAL _ Braves notebook. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   BBC-TEXAS-GUTSYPITCHER _ AUSTIN, Texas _ D.J. Jones tried to
convince himself that the pain in his gut did not exist. That was
no easy task, considering he pitched the entire spring with a
hernia the size of a baseball. Looking back, it seems incredible
that Jones pitched so effectively in his condition. (Cantu, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   AKERS _ Thirty-three-year-old defensive midfielder Michelle
Akers is the old warhorse of the U.S. women's soccer team but has
not lost her touch, scoring on a spectacular header against Nigeria
in the first round. Her 14-year national team career has included a
battle with chronic fatigue syndrome and no fewer than a dozen knee
surgeries. The born-again Christian has hinted that next summer's
Olympics probably will be the end of her career. The U.S. plays in
the quarterfinals of the Women's World Cup against Germany on
Thursday. (Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKN-DRAFT-PREVIEW _ Preview of the NBA draft (Bunn/Denberg,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-DRAFT-ADVANCE _ Huge centerpiece advancing Wednesday's
draft. Story focuses on Wally Szczerbiak and his dad. (Archdeacon,
Dayton Daily News). 35.
</P>
<P>
   BKO_MARV-ALBERT _ NBC re-hires Marv Albert as an announcer for
its National Basketball Association coverage, almost two years
after he was fired when he pleaded guilty to a misdemeanor assault
charge. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
