Frederic Weis (7-1); Duke sniper Trajan Langdon (6-2);
</P>
<P>
   18. Denver
</P>
<P>
   Needs: Small forward, real shooting guard
</P>
<P>
   Names: Posey; Minnesota's Quincy Lewis (6-7)
</P>
<P>
   19. Utah
</P>
<P>
   Needs: Athletes (preferably tall)
</P>
<P>
   Names: Miami skywalker Tim James (6-7); or UNLV's Shawn Marion
(6-7), in case rumors about dealing ex Long Beach Stater Bryon
Russell are true; Lewis
</P>
<P>
   20. Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   (See 17)
</P>
<P>
   21. Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   (See 20)
</P>
<P>
   22. Houston
</P>
<P>
   Needs: Point guard, inside help
</P>
<P>
   Names: A.J. Bramlett (6-11), a thin leaper from Arizona; Lari
Ketner (6-10), a thick sluggo from UMass
</P>
<P>
   23. LAKERS
</P>
<P>
   Needs: Power forward, point guard, someone to park karma
</P>
<P>
   Names: Nebraska's Venson Hamilton (6-10), the Big 12 Player of
the Year; Lewis or any of the above who slip down
</P>
<P>
   24. Utah
</P>
<P>
   See (19)
</P>
<P>
   25. Miami
</P>
<P>
   Needs: Shooting guard, inside depth
</P>
<P>
   Names: Kenny Thomas (6-8) from New Mexico; Ketner
</P>
<P>
   26. Indiana
</P>
<P>
   Needs: A center with healthy feet
</P>
<P>
   Name: Maybe Weis or Eschmeyer will be around
</P>
<P>
   27. Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   Needs: See 17, 20 and 21
</P>
<P>
   Name: If they haven't gone for a point guard yet, Stanford's
Arthur Lee (6-0) could go here
</P>
<P>
   28. Utah
</P>
<P>
   Needs: Anyone who can run and jump
</P>
<P>
   Name: Texas high-riser Kris Clack (6-5)
</P>
<P>
   29. San Antonio
</P>
<P>
   Needs: New arena, contract extension for Tim Duncan
</P>
<P>
   Name: One of the above who hasn't been chosen
</P>
